After installing extension, put LoHa file in your sd/models/lora folder and write LoRA notation in prompt to applying LoHa. <lora:your_loha_name:weight>

    • Racing competition costume :

    • SSR Speed (Wedding) :

    • Casual :

    • Tracen summer uniform :

items.name: Andrew Wyeth Style
items.description:
Andrew Wyeth was an American artist known for his realistic and evocative paintings, primarily in the medium of watercolor and tempera. He is considered one of the foremost figures of 20th-century American realism.

Wyeth's artwork often depicts rural landscapes, particularly the landscapes of Pennsylvania and Maine, where he spent much of his life. He had a deep connection to nature and the natural world, which is evident in his paintings. His compositions often feature desolate landscapes, weathered buildings, and solitary figures, conveying a sense of melancholy and introspection.

One of Wyeth's most famous works is "Christina's World," a painting that depicts a young woman lying in a field, looking towards a distant house. The painting has a dreamlike quality and has become an iconic image in American art.

Wyeth's approach to painting was highly detailed and meticulous. He had a remarkable ability to capture the textures and nuances of his subjects, whether it be the weathered wood of a barn or the delicate folds of fabric. His use of light and shadow added a sense of depth and mood to his paintings, enhancing the emotional impact of his work.

Throughout his career, Wyeth received numerous accolades and awards for his contributions to the art world. His paintings continue to be celebrated for their realism, emotional depth, and ability to capture the essence of the American landscape.

Andrew Wyeth's legacy as an artist is marked by his ability to evoke a sense of place and atmosphere through his detailed and emotionally charged paintings. His work continues to resonate with viewers, inviting them to contemplate the beauty and complexity of the natural world and the human experience.

items.name: CityEdge_2dToonMix
items.description:
後半に日本語の説明を入れています。

This is a 2D based Anime model (not using 2.5D approach). Targetting to realize both simplified and clear drawing and enough detail.

There are 3 variation for this model. Base model (v1.15), more outline version (v1 Line) and less outline version (v1 Flat). You can switch among them to optimize your output. No variation from ver3. Use outline LoRAs (plus or minus) for control outline.

Merged models are as follows.

  • Counterfeit v3

  • Anything v5

  • Falkons v1.2 created by Falcons

  • Contaby v2 created by PlayaEmblem

  • Koji

  • LinexDiffusion / ALLBoyMix (after version 3)

Both SFW and soft NSFW are capable. VAE is not needed but you can try some.

List of my models

  • CityEdgeMix : Simple photo-realistic model based on Chilled family

  • CityEdge_ToonMix : Simple 2.5D anime-like model based on CityEdgeMix

  • CityEdge_2dToonMix : Pure 2D anime-like model merging only 2D models

  • CityEdge_StyleMix : Anime-like model with detail depiction by making use of block-merge

  • CityEdge_FusionMix : 2.5D model focusing on unique depiction through merging many models and block-merge.

  • Landscape_Photoreal : Model that produces photorealistic output, whether with characters or just the background

  • CityEdge_DollyMix : Model that produces doll-like and 3D animated movie-like output

2Dベースのアニメ系モデルで、いわゆるリアルモデルによる2.5Dのアプローチを排除したモデルです。シンプルではっきりした塗りと細部の詳細な表現の両立を目指したモデルとなっています。

3つのバリエーションが用意されています。ベースモデル (v1.15)、輪郭線を強調したバージョン (v1 Line)、輪郭線を削ったバージョン (v1 Flat)です。好みに合わせて使い分けてください。 ver3でバリエーションをなくしました。アウトライン系LoRA（プラス／マイナス適用）で調整してください。

Counterfeit v3、Anything v5、Falkons v1.2(Falcons氏作)、Contaby v2(PlayaEmblem氏作）、Koji、LinexDiffusion(ver3以降)、ALLBoyMix(ver3以降)がマージベースです。

微エロおよび非エロに対応可。VAEは焼き込み済ですが別のものも試してみていいと思います。

モデル一覧

  • CityEdgeMix : Chilled系をベースにしたシンプルなフォトリアル系マージモデル

  • CityEdge_ToonMix : CityEdgeMixを2.5D化したシンプルな2.5Dアニメモデル

  • CityEdge_2dToonMix : 2Dモデルだけをマージしたピュア2Dアニメモデル

  • CityEdge_StyleMix : 階層マージを駆使してディテール描写にこだわったアニメモデル

  • CityEdge_FusionMix : 多数のモデルのマージと階層マージによる独自の描写にこだわった2.5Dモデル

  • Landscape_Photoreal : キャラクターがいても、背景だけでも、フォトリアルな出力が得られるモデル

  • CityEdge_DollyMix : ドール調・3Dアニメ映画調の出力が得られるモデル

items.name: Jane Rogers
items.description:
📝Biography📝

(generation advice below) 👇

🌟Jane Rogers 🌟

was born on July 3, 1998, in Phoenix, Arizona. With a height of 5 feet 9 inches and measurements of 34B-25-36, Jane Rogers is an exceptionally cute girl with sparkling green eyes and a bright smile. She is an intelligent and enthusiastic young woman who had a huge sexual experience before she started working in the porn industry. So far, Jane has made at least 80 scenes, and she is represented by the Motley Models agency.

Jane's basic motives for entering the industry were not fame or money, but pleasure. She started her adult career in the spring of 2019 when she was around 21 years old. Jane worked as an independent model for almost a year before joining Motley Models. Jane matured as a performer and filmed her best scenes in the following year. Jane has since worked with various notable people within the industry.

💡Generation Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling (Using auto1111 or similar UX) 🔧

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted between 0.65 to 1.

  • Lower weighting needed often for headshots.

  • Samples done with CyberRealistic v20 with sampling steps above 20, generally between 40 to 80 using Euler a, DPM++ SDE Karras and UniPC.

  • When testing a prompt, I often do a low lowres gen of multiple images, then choose the seed I like and upscale.

🚀Upscaling🚀

  • Portrait and close-ups work great using Hires. fix and 8X NMKD-Faces at 0.10 - .15 denoise strength.

  • Sometimes I just send it to Ultimate SD upscale after a quick render and run 2x at a scale of two, but often just the Hires. fix is good enough to capture enough details for the subject matter.

  • Ultimate SD upscale script used @ ~.15 - .4 denoising using 8x NMKD Faces or 4X UltraSharp redraw upscalers.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

  • The prompts continue to evolve. CyberRealistic is a reasonably flexible model for being realism focused and still capturing abstract concepts. I still think they have trumped the SD 1.5 game. 👑

  • Feedback appreciated. Please leave a review if you've used this LORA. 👍

  • Leave a comment if you are having issues getting good output, I'll try to respond.

items.description:
Dragon Age Absolution style LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕


I've been wanting to make this for a while, but this also happens to be a sponsored commission. I think it came up pretty accurate-

Should be used at around 1 weight with AnyLoRA ckpt and with the trigger dragonage style.

Keep in mind this is not a character LoRA, so it can't really reproduce characters from the show, but it can get pretty close with accurate prompting. This is very much intended for you to create your own characters. It should work on basically every model, but it's accurate only on AnyLoRA as far as I've seen, as that one tends to be more "style neutral".


How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)
